**Knowledge, Attitudes, and Practices (KAP) Survey on Atopic Dermatitis (AD) and Topical Treatments**

Dear Participant,

Thank you for your interest in participating in this scientific research. Before starting, please read the following information carefully. Your participation is completely voluntary, and you may withdraw at any time without any negative consequences.

**What is the purpose of this research?**
This survey aims to assess Knowledge, Attitudes, and Practices (KAP) among the general public regarding:
• Atopic dermatitis (eczema) as a chronic condition
• Available topical treatments (corticosteroids, moisturizers, natural therapies)
• Propolis as a natural therapeutic option before resorting to corticosteroids
• Prevalence of misdiagnosis of skin parasites (e.g., scabies) and consequences of self-treatment before medical diagnosis

**Scientific importance:** Results will contribute to understanding knowledge and behavioral gaps, and guide health awareness policies.

**Time required:** 10–15 minutes
**Number of questions:** 33 closed-ended + 4 open-ended questions

**There are no right or wrong answers — we only ask for your honest responses.**

**Important clarifications:**
• This survey does not include any medical intervention
• Complete confidentiality — your identity will not be identified or linked to your responses

🔒 **All responses are confidential and anonymous, and will be used for scientific research purposes only.**

