# QUESTIONNAIRE 2: HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONAL KAP SURVEY (ENGLISH)

**Knowledge, Attitudes, and Practices (KAP) Survey on Topical Corticosteroid Management in Atopic Dermatitis, Pruritic Parasitic Skin Infections, and the Role of Natural Preparations Containing Beeswax and Propolis**

Dear Doctors and Pharmacists,

This survey aims to assess knowledge, attitudes, and practices related to the therapeutic management of Atopic Dermatitis (AD) and eczema, with focus on cases associated with pruritic parasitic skin infections. The survey also explores the feasibility of adopting natural preparations based on beeswax and propolis (Beeswax + Propolis) as an adjunct option in dermatological management.

Data will be used for scientific research purposes only, with guaranteed complete confidentiality and no publication of any personal information. Participation is voluntary, and the survey takes approximately 5-7 minutes.

Thank you for your cooperation, which contributes to improving clinical practices in dermatology.

